reviews.review_text: Nice! This AUD is just as good as the even more recent Matrix, and it's a helluva show. Garcia & Lesh are very on, playing with psychedelic intricacy. Tons of cowboy songs in the first set, but still. Not sure how I like the pairing of Lost/Althea, but they're both awesome renditions anyway. This must be one of the first Lost Sailors, as it doesn't even have the oohs in it yet. I love the way they start Scarlet quiet and then crash into it as soon as the lyrics start. The Phil jam out of Eyes is sweet, and then Hamza comes out. Very otherworldly.
